messages.message:
Hey team! i'm cleaning up our enablement material for private preview (we have gotten a lot of asks from GTM to better clarify what's in and what's out).

Wanted to double click on file support:
Support for *most common file types* up to *50MB/800 pages:* .pdf, .png, .jpg, .docx, .doc, .eml, .msg, .xlsx, .csv, .tiff

Are there any limitations we're actively aware of for files above? I think we still need to optimize TIFFs? cc: @Abhishek Adupa /@tony.shi

.pdf - upto 50MB (45 MB is safe) - 800 pages is safe
https://aihub-sandbox.internal.instabase.com/review/F78ad20e-74f4-4352-827d-bfbd83b61a94
Ran with 45 MB - 600 pages for testing - ran successfully.
Rest should support the same limits. TIFF is the one that might need some work.
Can you clarify "need some work"? Might be reasonable to say it's not officially supported if we think we might still hit errors etc.
